  <para>
  As software developers and system administrators, you may need to adapt various aspects of the &selnx; policy for specialized workloads and deployment scenarios.
  This is because of the design principles of the <emphasis>targeted</emphasis> policy, as seen in <xref linkend="selinux-policy-targeted"/>.
  </para>
  <para>
  Design principles include:
  </para>
  <itemizedlist>
    <listitem>
      <para>
       Adjusting network port contexts
      </para>
    </listitem>
    <listitem>
      <para>
       Managing policy modules
      </para>
    </listitem>
    <listitem>
      <para>
       Defining and modifying file contexts
      </para>
    </listitem>
    <listitem>
      <para>
      Controlling policy behavior via booleans
      </para>
    </listitem>
    <listitem>
      <para>
      Setting domains to <literal>permissive</literal> mode for troubleshooting
      </para>
    </listitem>
    <listitem>
      <para>
     Enabling or disabling <literal>dontaudit</literal>rules to enhance policy development or auditing
      </para>
    </listitem>
  </itemizedlist>
 </para>
</topic>
